Living shadow
hit die: 2d4+con
+3 dex
+1 in any
+1 in any other 
You are a shadow and therefore do not have any contours. You can change appearance as you want but not change from the size medium. Any attack against you has disadvantage. You need to sleep 2 hours when the sun is at the highest peak but other than that you don’t need to. 

Jumping to shadows 
uses: equal to dex modifier
recharge: long rest
You can jump to another creature's shadow within line of sight and you then get a surprise attack for free against the creature.

Jump with friendly shadows
uses: 3 times
Recharge: long rest
You can “teleport” to an allies shadow no matter the distance and you don’t need to see your ally.
You can choose an ally equal to your dex modifier. 

Attacks
When you hit a creature with an attack you deal one extra d8 and you also roll on a table each time you hit a creature with an unarmed strike (that has CR over 2). A weapon you are holding is always dark in color

Table 
1=deal magical damage
2=+dex*2
3=+1d20
4=cast Chill Touch against the target
5=you can jump to another creatures shadow
6=Make two extra attacks
7= you regain hp equal to your damage this attack
8= you can teleport for free to an allies shadow if you want
 




Shadow weapon
you can target a weapon you can see. Your weapon becomes the same weapon with the same damages but is black and weight 0 grams but only you can hold it. If someone else tries the weapon just goes straight through their hands and disappears. you can store up to 3 weapons this way to shift between. When you choose a new over these 3 you need to replace one of the old ones. When copying any magical effects does not copy.
